{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W4XBwpXdvMfegJptvA6984","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the key issue. The logs from crdb-cluster-0 show:\n1. Node 1 (crdb-cluster-0) has been initialized - it has data and is running\n2. Node 2 (crdb-cluster-2) is reporting \"node waiting for init\" - it's a new node that hasn't joined the cluster yet\n3. The cluster is having leaseholder issues\n\nThe cluster seems to have been initialized previously (it has data) but nodes 1 and 2 (crdb-cluster-1 and crdb-cluster-2) were just killed and restarted. The new pods are starting fresh and the cluster is struggling.\nThe real problem is that crdb-cluster-0 was running solo as node 1 after the other pods were killed, which means it lost quorum. Now the fresh pods are coming back online, but one of them is stuck waiting for initialization because the cluster can't reach consensus to add it. So the \"node waiting for init\" message that node 0 is receiving from node 2 means that pod 2 restarted with a fresh or empty store, and since it's part of an already-initialized cluster, it's stuck waiting for initialization. This could happen if the PVC was cleared or if the node's store ID changed after the restart. I need to check whether the other pods actually retained their data or if they're starting fresh.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4911,"cache_read_input_tokens":32247,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4911},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4f25bfa-c061-44f5-97ce-536a57bdfbc1","uuid":"1532d7b2-294d-455c-bf61-01ec4e587ef9","request_id":"req_011CcbisatxP9wUGwaSJHffb"}
