{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Q14HFRf8VTfm2dN9JGSuRt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cluster is fully healthy. Here's what was found and fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** The StatefulSet command used a conditional to bind `crdb-cluster-1`'s HTTP server to `127.0.0.1:8080` (loopback only):\n```bash\nif [ \"$POD_NAME\" = \"crdb-cluster-1\" ]; then\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"127.0.0.1:8080\";\nelse\n  HTTP_ADDR=\"0.0.0.0:8080\";\nfi\n```\n\nKubernetes health probes connect via the pod's cluster IP, not loopback — so every liveness and readiness probe on pod 1 returned \"connection refused,\" causing Kubernetes to repeatedly kill and restart it. This destabilized the cluster by breaking quorum and triggering liveness epoch failures on the other nodes.\n\n**Fix:** Patched the StatefulSet to remove the conditional, binding all pods to `0.0.0.0:8080`. The StatefulSet rolling update then cleanly replaced all pods.\n\n**Verification:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running`\n- All 3 nodes: `is_available=true, is_live=true`\n- SQL: `SELECT 1` succeeds"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":807,"cache_read_input_tokens":76064,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":807},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a4f25bfa-c061-44f5-97ce-536a57bdfbc1","uuid":"f13c4842-2af7-43be-a491-680cbad939e0","request_id":"req_011CcbmB7A5FXSYQHS7dHuak"}
